When a folder is initialized with `dolt` a `.dolt` folder is created with the following structure:

```
├── config.json
├── noms
│   ├── LOCK
│   ├── du3j18uvnqhcvl78vd80kcj775r6
│   ├── manifest
│   └── oldgen
│       ├── LOCK
│       ├── hgjgg625u0much0n22uu4hnoa
│       └── manifest
├── repo_state.json
└── temptf
```

Now, the`repo_sate.json` is basically a file that keeps the information about the state of the current folder:

```
{
  "head": "refs/heads/master",
  "staged": "p1k4jrelqtkn88r0dogd3tb84fl",
  "working": "p1k4jrelqtkn88r0dogd3tb84fl",
  "merge": null,
  "remotes": {
    "origin": {
      "name": "origin",
      "url": "https://doltremoteapi.dolthub.com/camilogarciabotero/TestDolt",
      "fetch_specs": [
        "refs/heads/*:refs/remotes/origin/*"
      ],
      "params": {}
    }
  },
  "branches": {
    "master": {
      "head": "refs/heads/master",
      "remote": "origin"
    }
  }
}%  
```

Then my guess is that an `omz` theme could parse for a `.dolt` folder and look out the `repo_state.json` to get insights from the current state of the folder. Hope this information is useful. Note, this is the case of a repo that has a remote connection with `dolthub` (basically the dolt's github)

@carlosala Hey! I'll try to explain :) 
1 - earlier it was a rake task, but in the last versions of the rails framework it was migrated to the rails command, so now the rake task doesn't work anymore
2 - currently in the rails plugin for OMZ it is defined as a rake task, so we just need to change rake to rails command

more info:
_p9k_preexec1 () {
        _p9k_restore_special_params
        (( ${+functions[TRAPINT]} )) || trap - INT
}
_zsh_highlight_preexec_hook () {
        typeset -g _ZSH_HIGHLIGHT_PRIOR_BUFFER=
        typeset -gi _ZSH_HIGHLIGHT_PRIOR_CURSOR=
}
omz_termsupport_preexec () {
        [[ "${DISABLE_AUTO_TITLE:-}" != true ]] || return
        emulate -L zsh
        setopt extended_glob
        local -a cmdargs
        cmdargs=("${(z)2}")
        if [[ "${cmdargs[1]}" = fg ]]
        then
                local job_id jobspec="${cmdargs[2]#%}"
                case "$jobspec" in
                        (<->) job_id=${jobspec}  ;;
                        ("" | % | +) job_id=${(k)jobstates[(r)*:+:*]}  ;;
                        (-) job_id=${(k)jobstates[(r)*:-:*]}  ;;
                        ([?]*) job_id=${(k)jobtexts[(r)*${(Q)jobspec}*]}  ;;
                        (*) job_id=${(k)jobtexts[(r)${(Q)jobspec}*]}  ;;
                esac
                if [[ -n "${jobtexts[$job_id]}" ]]
                then
                        1="${jobtexts[$job_id]}"
                        2="${jobtexts[$job_id]}"
                fi
        fi
        local CMD="${1[(wr)^(*=*|sudo|ssh|mosh|rake|-*)]:gs/%/%%}"
        local LINE="${2:gs/%/%%}"
        title "$CMD" "%100>...>${LINE}%<<"
}
_p9k_preexec2 () {
        _p9k__preexec_cmd=$2
        _p9k__timer_start=EPOCHREALTIME
}

